title.narrative: MTR - CHILD PROTECTION IN HUMANITARIAN ACTION

description.narrative: MTR - COs capacity strengthened to support policies, programmes and advocacy to provide prevention or response services for children affected by humanitarian crises including armed conflict.,which contributes to Access To Justice, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Protect Every Child from Violence and Exploitation By 2021, UNICEF supported countries apply relevant policies, innovative approaches and evidence, to design and implement publicly and privately funded development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that Protect Every Child from Violence and Exploitation
